# Slice milestones — user confirmation required

Do **not** check off Slice milestones, mark roadmap items **Done / Shipped / verified**, or rewrite status tables in `docs/ROADMAP.md` / `TODO.md` as complete based only on:

- compile success
- contract / deploy gate passing
- agent assumption that a feature “should work”

## Rule

1. After implementing a slice (or G1/F1-style sub-milestone), leave status as **in progress / implemented — awaiting in-game confirm** (or leave checkboxes unchecked).
2. Only mark **Done**, **Shipped**, **verified in-game**, or tick `[x]` when the **user explicitly confirms** it works in-game (or explicitly asks you to mark it done).
3. Docs may note “deployed; contracts pass” without claiming milestone completion.
4. If the user reports a failure, keep or revert the milestone to incomplete — do not leave a false “Done”.

## Example

```markdown
; ❌ BAD — agent marks Done after deploy only
| **G** | Bed corpse… | **Done** — G1 verified |

; ✅ GOOD — wait for user
| **G** | Bed corpse… | **G1 implemented** — awaiting in-game confirm |
```
